<br>
I'd say roughly 70 percent of the MOB's in EQ are &quot;warrior-type&quot;, or at least somehow work on the warrior-style concept.  This isn't a hard number, just from my observations over the last couple years. <br>
<br>
Now, keeping that in mind, doesn't the game change dramatically when you change the dominant population?  <br>
<br>
I guess the connection I'm trying to draw here is along the lines of the patch a few months back where caster-NPC's can now use spells appropriate to their level.  This change did have an impact in some encounters (I remember the first time that ice comet stung me for a quick 1200 dmg).<br>
<br>
Wouldn't it make the game much harder if 70 percent of the MOB's were upgraded in some sense based on a warrior-added ability, whether offensively or defensively? <br>
<br>
Now I'm fully aware that MOB's aren't the same as Player-made characters, but they are designed along the same &quot;general&quot; idea.  <br>
<br>
Imagine if that Froglok suddenly had a new mitigation table, making him 10-15 percent harder to hit.  A change like that would certainly wreak havoc on many aspects of the game. <br>
<br>
I think I've explained my brainstorm correctly... dunno, kinda' tired.  Let me know if this makes sense to any of you guys and gals.      <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=283443" target="_blank">
